phoresis, elevated creatine phosphokinase levels, and hyperpyrexia. Patients should seek prompt medical attention if they experience symptoms that could indicate the occurrence of torsade de pointes such as dizziness, lightheadedness, fainting, palpitation, irregular heart rhythm, shortness of breath, or syncope.', 'Synergism', 'The use of deutetrabenazine in combination with neuroleptic agents or other dopamine antagonists should preferable be avoided.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/73805/', '', 'Inotersen, Riluzole, Tafamidis', '', 1767369485);
